President Biden visited a clinic to promote COVID-19 vaccinations for children and expressed gratitude for the healthcare workers. He announced that the United States is the first country to offer safe and effective vaccines for children as young as six months old. He assured parents that the vaccines are safe and encouraged them to get their children vaccinated. The President also addressed concerns about energy prices and the oil and gas industry, stating that there is a need for more refining capacity and a transition to renewable energy. He mentioned the possibility of a federal gas tax holiday and plans to have a conversation with President Xi of China. The President confirmed that his planned trip to Israel is unaffected by recent events. He also mentioned ongoing discussions about addressing inflation and the need for more funding for vaccine campaigns and future pandemics.